    <mads:note type="source">Smith's Dictionary of Greek and Roman Biography and Mythology, 
        Vol , 1867, p. 188: "Antigonus, of Carystus, is supposed by some to have lived in the 
        reign of Ptolemaeus Philadelphus, and by others in that of Euergetes. Respecting his 
        life nothing is known but we possess by him a work called ἱστοριῶν παραδόξων συναγωγή
        (Historiae Mirabiles)....THe Anthologia Graeca (ix. 406) contains an epigram of Antigonus..."
    </mads:note>
